public interface SchemeSymbol
extends java.io.Serializable

A SchemeSymbol is an object that can be defined or not. SchemeSymbols are created using the REPL.internSchemeSymbol(string) and are initially undefined. Its value can be queried and set. Getting the value of an undefined SchemeSymbol throws an error. method. Getting
